results.name: Number of connected matchstick graphs on n nodes.
link: Jaskaran Singh Grover, Changliu Liu, Katia Sycara, Deadlock Analysis and Resolution for Multi-Robot Systems, (2020).
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Connected Graph
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Matchstick Graph
example: a(6) is one less than A059103(6) because the 3-prism graph Y_3 cannot be drawn in an embedding that is both planar and unit-distance.
There appear to be 13 connected graphs on 7 nodes that are unit-distance but non-matchstick (including Y_3+e and the Moser spindle).
